## ðŸš€ Quick Start

```python
import restalker

# Define which elements we desire (e.g., Tor URLs)
s = restalker.reStalker(tor=True, i2p=True)
elements = s.parse(input_text)

for element in elements:
    print(f"[*] Darknet IOC found: {element}")
```

---

## ðŸŽ¯ Detection Capabilities

`reStalker` can extract these entities from any binary or text source:

### ðŸ” Credentials & Identity

- **Base64** encoded data
- **Username** patterns
- **Password** patterns  
- **Phone** numbers
- **Email** addresses
- **Personal names**

### ðŸ’° Digital Assets & Cryptocurrencies

- **BTC** (Bitcoin) wallet addresses
- **ETH** (Ethereum) wallet addresses
- **XMR** (Monero) wallet addresses
- **ZEC** (Zcash) wallet addresses
- **DASH** wallet addresses
- **DOT** (Polkadot) wallet addresses
- **XRP** (Ripple) wallet addresses
- **BNB** (Binance) wallet addresses

### ðŸ“± Social Networks & Communication

- **Twitter/X** account handles
- **Telegram** URLs
- **WhatsApp** URLs
- **Skype** URLs
- **Tox ID** identifiers
- **Session ID** identifiers

### ðŸ” Cryptographic Hashes

- **MD5** hash values
- **SHA1** hash values
- **SHA256** hash values

### ðŸ’³ Financial Information

- **BIN** (Bank Identification Numbers)
- **Credit Card** numbers

### ðŸŒ Dark Web & Alternative Networks

- **Tor** (.onion) URLs
- **I2P** URLs
- **Freenet** URLs
- **ZeroNet** URLs
- **IPFS** URLs

### ðŸ“‹ Paste Sites & Code Sharing

- **justpaste.it** links
- **pastebin.com** links
- **pasted.co** links
- **hastebin.com** links
- **snipt.org** links
- **gist.github.com** links
- **telegra.ph** links
- **ghostbin.com** links

